                    "company": "Solidaridad Network",
                    "description": "I am responsible for Solidaridad\u2019s European and global fashion agenda for policy influencing and market uptake, with a focus on influencing the private sector to commit to and implement responsible environmental management, decent work and fair value distribution within their supply chain, and the public sector to enforce national norms and regulatory frameworks for sustainability and due diligence. Collectively with and through (multistakeholder) initiatives like the SAC, SLCP, BCI, OCA, AII and the Policy Hub, but also directly with brands and manufacturers. Influencing the EU strategy for sustainable and circular textiles, the corporate sustainable due diligence directive and other relevant legislative proposals, I am mainly doing through consultations, position papers, letters and meetings with policy makers. \n\nAs the Lead of our global cotton and textiles community of practitioners, I am responsible for our global linking and learning agenda and work with the team, brands, facilities, and farmers to implement environmental and social improvement programs like the Better Mill initiative and the Wage Management Systems program. I represent Solidaridad internationally on events, in panels, on conferences, and act as our spokesperson in the media. \n\nMain focus countries for Solidaridad\u2019s programs: Bangladesh, China, Egypt, Ethiopia, India, Indonesia, Mozambique, Zambia\n\nSolidaridad's mission it to bring together supply chain actors and engage them in innovative solutions to improve production, ensuring the transition to a sustainable and inclusive economy that maximizes the benefit for all.\n\nwww.solidaridadnetwork.org\nwww.solidaridad.nl",
                    "title": "Senior Policy Director Sustainable Fashion",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
            ]
